on Qunut: Supplication of Umar during persecution","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 15, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Ubaid ibn Umair reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, supplicated after bowing in prayer and he said, \u201cO Allah, forgive the believing men and believing women and the Muslim men and Muslim women, bring their hearts together and reconcile between them, support them against Your enemies\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":27238,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/03\/07\/umar-lament-wept-wealth\/","url_meta":{"origin":20734,"position":3},"title":"Umar on Wealth: The Caliph laments when he finds treasure","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 7, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Rajab reported: When the treasures of Khosrau were opened for Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, he wept and he said, \u201cVerily, the likes of this were never opened for people but that Allah made it a source of enmity between them.\u201d Source: Kashf al-Kurbah 1\/318\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":3654,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/07\/13\/prophet-daiya-dawah-taxes\/","url_meta":{"origin":20734,"position":4},"title":"Umar II on Da&#8217;wah: The Prophet is caller to Allah, not tax collector","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 13, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Kathir reported: Umar ibn Abdul Aziz, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cVerily, Allah has only sent Muhammad, peace and blessings be upon him, as a preacher. He did not send him as a tax collector.\u201d Source: al-Bida\u0304yah wal-Niha\u0304yah 13\/667 \u0639\u0646 \u0627\u0628\u0646 \u0643\u062b\u064a\u0631 \u0642\u0627\u0644 \u0639\u0645\u0631 \u0628\u0646 \u0639\u0628\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0632\u064a\u0632\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":26014,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2018\/03\/04\/big-belly-punishment-not-blessing\/","url_meta":{"origin":20734,"position":5},"title":"Umar on Gluttony: A large belly is a punishment, not a blessing","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 4, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Hasan reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, saw a man with a large belly and he said, \u201cWhat is this?\u201d The man said, \u201cIt is a blessing from Allah.\u201d Umar said, \u201cNo, rather it is a punishment.\u201d Source: H\u0323adi\u0304th Muh\u0323ammad ibn \u2018Abd Alla\u0304h al-Ans\u0323a\u0304ri\u0304 42 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/20734","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href"